request.description:
Returns all 6 subcategories as a flat list, each with their variables as `children`.

This is a flat alternative to the nested category tree.

**Response shape:**
```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "uuid",
      "name": "Heritage Buildings",
      "children": [
        { "id": "uuid", "name": "Number of Building" }
      ]
    },
    ...
  ]
}
```

Returns all 18 regions without their city children. Useful when you only need region-level selection.

**Response shape:**
```json
{
  "data": [
    { "id": "uuid", "name": "Ayeyarwady" },
    ...
  ]
}
```

Returns Buddhist population count for Bogale city in 2019.

**Verified response includes:**
```json
{
  "data": [{
    "category": { "name": "Standard of Living" },
    "subCategory": [{
      "subCat": { "name": "Religion" },
      "variable_city": {
        "buddhist": [{
          "id": "uuid",
          "name": "Buddhist",
          "city_name": "Bogale",
          "value": "313483"
        }]
      }
    }]
  }]
}
```

Note: `category.name` shows `Standard of Living` due to loop bug — actual data is from Demographic category.
